 Minikube install in amazon linuX server
 
 Step 1: Install Required Dependencies

sudo dnf install -y curl wget conntrack git
Optional but recommended if you’ll use Docker:

sudo dnf install -y docker
sudo systemctl enable --now docker
sudo usermod -aG docker ec2-user
newgrp docker

✅ Step 2: Install kubectl

curl -LO "https://dl.k8s.io/release/$(curl -s https://dl.k8s.io/release/stable.txt)/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl"
chmod +x kubectl
sudo mv kubectl /usr/local/bin/
kubectl version --clientclient


✅ Step 3: Install minikube

curl -LO https://storage.googleapis.com/minikube/releases/latest/minikube-linux-amd64
sudo install minikube-linux-amd64 /usr/local/bin/minikube
minikube version
✅ Step 4: Start Minikube
Now start Minikube using the Docker driver:
 
minikube start --driver=docker --force
If you're not using Docker, you can also try the none driver (for bare-metal install):

sudo minikube start --driver=none
⚠️ Note: The --driver=none option runs Kubernetes components directly on the host, which may need root permissions and can conflict with other services.

✅ Step 5: Verify Minikube

kubectl get nodes
You should see the Minikube node in Ready state.
